data.name: txtPreGapLength.ToolTip
data.value: Pregap is a certain amount of silence or hidden audio before track one. Normally it is known from the CUE sheet, but if converting/verifying a set of separate tracks without a CUE sheet you might want to set this.

data.name: txtDataTrackLength.ToolTip
data.value: Not used for normal music CDs. Enhanced CDs with data tracks cannot be found in database unless you know the length of the data track. You can often find it in EAC log. If EAC log is found next to the CUE sheet, it will be parsed automatically and you won't have to enter anything here.
